"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Dez 03, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104mez1665702540201.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/mez1665702540201.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/mez1665702540201.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"mez1665702540201\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"mez1665702540201__webdefinitions_248259\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Use the current component to load channels in <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$webinfo</span>.</p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"mez1665702540201__topic_d79376e1_d79377e1_d79378e1\">\n<div class=\"p\" id=\"mez1665702540201__p_d79379e1_d79380e1_d79381e1\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" id=\"mez1665702540201__codeblock_vvt_tcz_bwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">webdefinitions</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"mez1665702540201__topic_d52197e1_d52198e1_d52199e1_d52200e1_d52201e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1147547e68\">\n                       \n Use\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"mez1665702540201__d6025e20\">Use in Dynamic Server Page components.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"mez1665702540201__topic_d52202e1_d52203e1_d52204e1_d52205e1_d52206e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1147547e77\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">webdefinitions</span> loads the following information into\n               <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$webinfo</span> channels:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"mez1665702540201__ul_c35_vcz_bwb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"mez1665702540201__li_d33521e1_d33522e1_d33523e1\">Component definitions for the current component\n               are loaded into the <code class=\"ph codeph\">Definitions</code> channel. These definitions can\n               include properties, initial values, and valrep lists.</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"mez1665702540201__li_d33524e1_d33525e1_d33526e1\">Names of JavaScript files for the current\n               component's web widgets are loaded into the <code class=\"ph codeph\">JavaScript</code> channel.</li>\n<li class=\"li\">Names of JavaScript module files for the current component's web widgets are loaded\n               into the <code class=\"ph codeph\">Module</code> channel.</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"mez1665702540201__li_d33527e1_d33528e1_d33529e1\">All references to CSS files in the current\n               component are loaded into the <code class=\"ph codeph\">css</code> channel.</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"mez1665702540201__p_d79397e1_d79398e1_d79399e1\">By default, the data is appended to each channel. This\n            allows multiple component definitions to be handled by one channel without ProcScript\n            intervention. If this behavior is not expected, you must explicitly clear each channel\n            before calling <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">webdefinitions</span>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"mez1665702540201__p_d79400e1_d79401e1_d79402e1\">The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">webdefinitions</span> statement\n            ensures that CSS, JavaScript, and Module channels do not contain duplicate references to\n            CSS, JavaScript, or Module files.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"mez1665702540201__section_d35_vcz_bwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1147547e131\">Example: postActivate Trigger for DSP</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">The default code of the DSP postActivate trigger generates the initial\n            page or a page updated, depending on the value of <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$webresponsetype</span>.\n            The following example shows a simplified version of this code (excluding the error\n            handling.)</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104mez1665702540201_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"mez1665702540201__codeblock_fxs_5cz_bwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">trigger postActivate\nselectcase $webresponsetype\ncase \"UPDATE\" ; Update page\n websave ; Generate data\ncase \"FULLPAGE\" ; Initial page\n weblayout ; Generate layout\n webdefinitions ; Generate component definitions\n websave ; Generate data\nendselectcase\nend; postActivate</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<div class=\"div\">\n<p class=\"p\">In this example <span class=\"ph filepath\">myScript.js</span> is assigned to\n                  <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$webinfo</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">(\"javascript\")</code>. When <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">webdefinitions</span> is called,\n               the necessary JavaScripts for the current component are added.</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104mez1665702540201_html_1\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"mez1665702540201__codeblock_cs3_ycz_bwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">; assign mySscript.js\n$webinfo(\"javascript\") = \"myScript.js\"\nputmess $webinfo(\"javascript\")\n; only myscript.js is printed\n; Running web definitions appends the default javascript files. \nwebdefinitions</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fyu1665702539304.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$webinfo</a><p>Return or set information about the current HTTP request or response.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529886\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529886\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "webdefinitions Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Dez 03, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Use the current component to load channels in $webinfo . webdefinitions Copy Use Use in Dynamic Server Page components. Description webdefinitions loads the following information into $webinfo channels: Component definitions for the current component are loaded into the Definitions channel. These definitions can include properties, initial values, and valrep lists. Names of JavaScript files for the current component's web widgets are loaded into the JavaScript channel. Names of JavaScript module files for the current component's web widgets are loaded into the Module channel. All references to CSS files in the current component are loaded into the css channel. By default, the data is appended to each channel. This allows multiple component definitions to be handled by one channel without ProcScript intervention. If this behavior is not expected, you must explicitly clear each channel before calling webdefinitions . The webdefinitions statement ensures that CSS, JavaScript, and Module channels do not contain duplicate references to CSS, JavaScript, or Module files. Example: postActivate Trigger for DSP The default code of the DSP postActivate trigger generates the initial page or a page updated, depending on the value of $webresponsetype . The following example shows a simplified version of this code (excluding the error handling.) Explain this code trigger postActivate selectcase $webresponsetype case \"UPDATE\" ; Update page websave ; Generate data case \"FULLPAGE\" ; Initial page weblayout ; Generate layout webdefinitions ; Generate component definitions websave ; Generate data endselectcase end; postActivate Copy In this example myScript.js is assigned to $webinfo (\"javascript\") . When webdefinitions is called, the necessary JavaScripts for the current component are added. Explain this code ; assign mySscript.js $webinfo(\"javascript\") = \"myScript.js\" putmess $webinfo(\"javascript\") ; only myscript.js is printed ; Running web definitions appends the default javascript files. webdefinitions Copy Related Links $webinfo Return or set information about the current HTTP request or response. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}